fields.title: Update from one table to another using two DBs
fields.body:
UPDATE 
`porta-billing`.DID_Numbers PB_DID
JOIN
`testdb`.DID_Numbers T_DID
ON
PB_DID.i_did_number=T_DID.i_did_number
SET
PB_DID.i_customer=T_DID.i_customer, PB_DID.customer_markup=T_DID.customer_markup, PB_DID.released = T_DID.released
WHERE
PB_DID.i_customer in (<all customers>);

Update with Join

UPDATE Customers CS 
JOIN Invoices INV
ON CS.i_customer = INV.i_customer
SET CS.unallocated_payments = CS.unallocated_payments - INV.payments
WHERE
INV.issue_date >= '2017-07-01'
AND CS.i_customer in (432, 6176, 40439, 66333, 66446, 66618, 66914, 67076, 67180, 67227, 67394, 16);

LogFormat "%h [%P] %{PB_USERNAME}e %t \"%r\" %>s %b \"%{PB_ACCOUNT_ID}e\" \"%{PB_SELFCARE}e\" %D %{SOAPAction}i" custom_format
%h - Remote hostname
%P - The process ID of the child that serviced the request.
%t - Time the request was received

%b - Size of response in bytes
